wide variety of industrial equipment increased 92 percent to 
228 billion after a 104 percent decline in july 
the closely watched nondefense capital goods sector fell 98 
percent to 374 billion economists use this category as a 
barometer of business investment plans 
orders for both electrical machinery and primary metals 
including steel were down last month the department said 
electrical machinery orders fell 09 percent to 196 billion 
with communications equipment showing the largest decrease 
primary metals were off 19 percent to 113 billion 
excluding the defense category which swings widely from month 
to month orders rose 39 percent in august after falling 15 
percent in july 
volatile military orders increased 19 percent to 78 billion 
after plunging 147 percent in july 
shipments of durable goods in august rose a record 95 percent 
to 1284 billion much of it reflecting automobiles the previous 
high during the current sevenyear economic expansion was a 45 
percent increase in january 1983 
