slovenia which borders italy austria and hungary is the most 
prosperous and westwardlooking of yugoslavias six constituent 
republics it has already allowed an unprecedented degree of 
democratization including the formation of several independent 
political parties 
yugoslavias state and communist party leadership has criticized 
the amendments as being contrary to the federal constitution 
the collective state presidency in charge of the armed forces 
said monday it will use all legal measures to prevent the 
adoption of the amendments indicating it might proclaim a state of 
emergency in the northern republic 
slovenias central committee said today there are no 
convincing reasons for delaying the adoption of the amendments nor 
do they conflict with the yugoslav constitution 
the slovenian communists said according to the tanjug news 
agency that the amendments do not represent a danger for the 
future of yugoslavia 
the yugoslav federation is not being endangered by those 
demanding additional guarantees for the respect of the equality and 
sovereignty of its people 
a recent public opinion poll conducted in the republic said that 
more than 70 percent of slovenes favor the constitutional changes 
despite warnings by the eightmember presidency that the vote on 
the changes must be postponed slovenian parliament president miran 
potrc said he was certain the slovenian legislature will adopt the 
amendments 
