an east german emissary today told 
east germans holed up in the west german embassy that they can 
legally emigrate to the west but first must return home a 
spokesmen for the refugees said 
wolfgang vogel arrived today to speak to representatives of 
about 1200 east germans who have crowded the garden of the west 
german embassy in hopes of obtaining safe passage to the west 
after meeting with vogel between 50 and 60 east germans boarded 
a bus that reportedly took them to a prague railroad station for 
their journey back to east germany the others however remained 
in the embassy quarters and it was unclear if they refused the east 
german offer 
