it was after solving the case of the brucepartington plans that 
sherlock holmes completed his monograph on the polyphonic motets of 
lassus experts according to dr watson rated it the last word 
upon the subject 
its unlikely that lassus motets will ever be exhausted he 
composed 700 or so of which only a few dozen have been recorded 
in addition to his 60 settings of the mass 101 settings of the 
magnificat plus hundreds of madrigals and chansons 
born in 1530 lassus was perhaps the most popular composer of 
his time he not only wrote a lot of music he wrote well as two 
new recordings prove 
the choir of christ church cathedral offers two mass settings 
three motets and a madrigal 
the missa venatorum barely 10 minutes long shows lassus at his 
most economical the kind of music that might elevate the mind 
without aggravating the knees 
technically the oxford choir cannot match the tallis scholars 
professional polish but it is closer to the sound lassus would 
have known 
the missa osculetur me recorded by the tallis scholars 
illustrates lassus frequent technique of musical parody in this 
case the mass reworks his own motet set to the opening verses of 
the song of solomon let him kiss me 
