unless we do much more to conserve our global environment he 
said singling out a reduction in carbon monoxide emissions which 
contribute to global warming as a goal 
he also said the third world which spends 200 billion a year 
on defense more than its combined expenditure on health and 
education must devote fewer resources to the military if it 
expects to prosper 
developing countries on one side and their arms suppliers and 
creditors on the other must adapt to a world where budgets are 
tight he said in evaluating their military expenditures 
governments should be realistic but they also should remember the 
human consequences of these choices 
