<TEXT>
the face of general motors corps minivans has 
undergone plastic surgery and chrysler corp may not like gms nose 
job 
ever since small passenger vans caught the fancy of american 
buyers chrysler has commanded a dominant share of the market gm 
is hoping its longhooded minivans will compel chrysler owners to 
switch makes 
while the auto market as a whole likely will shrink during the 
next year there are predictions of continued growth in minivans a 
segment which has seen rapid expansion since 1983 when chrysler 
introduced the dodge caravan and the plymouth voyager 
