thinks the new gm minivans are quite attractive 
the frontwheeldrive vehicles join the conventionally styled 
chevrolet astro which is being offered in fourwheel drive for 
1990 in the assault on chryslers hold on the minivan market all 
chryslers minivans are frontwheel drive 
its the biggest threat that chrysler minivans have received 
to date brady said there really hasnt been anything that 
would serve as a direct substitute the others have either been 
smaller or rearwheel drive 
the minivan battle isnt just between gm and chrysler 
ford continues to offer its aerostar and japanese companies are 
hoping to grab larger pieces of the minivan pie 
chrysler isnt sitting still either it is offering a town amp 
country version of the minivan more expensive than the caravan or 
voyager but loaded with extras including leather seats and a 
compass 
well sell out two minivan plants lutz said speaking of 
the st louis mo and windsor ontario factories 
