<TEXT>
international business machines corp tuesday 
revealed ambitious plans for micro channel architecture its 
patentcovered design for the way information moves around inside 
its personal computers 
ibm also said that micro channel is theoretically capable of 
transferring data at 160 million bytes per second eight times as 
fast as its current speed limit a byte represents one letter or 
number 
the announcements were intended in part to counter the momentum 
of a standard that is being pushed by the gang of nine rival 
makers of personal computers such as compaq computer corp 
advanced logic research inc recently said it will begin 
shipping the first computer built to that rival standard in october 
ibm said it intends to use micro channel not only with personal 
computers but eventually with highspeed workstations and even 
mainframe computers a landmark in the growing importance of 
personal computers 
although ibms mainframe line uses a different system for 
internal data transfer the company said micro channel would 
eventually become the way that mainframes communicate with personal 
computers and workstations 
as a sign of the micro channels importance ibm said the design 
would form the heart of a new line of workstations that will 
replace the relatively unsuccessful rt pc late this year or early 
in 1990 
ibm has tried to make micro channel into an industry standard 
but companies that have come out with compatible machines under 
license to ibm have had limited success ibm is hoping that 
tuesdays announcements will convince customers that micro channel 
announced in 1987 is the wave of the future 
theyre trying to show a sense of order in a potentially 
chaotic environment said sam albert a former ibm executive who 
is now a consultant in scarsdale ny 
ibms rivals say their personal computer standard is better 
because there are more addon devices that will work with it but 
ibm said there are more than 1000 addon devices made by other 
companies to enhance the ibm personal system2 and more in the 
works 
in addition intel corp and chips and technologies inc both 
said tuesday they were working with ibm on developing sets of chips 
that other companies could use to make compatible addon devices 
for the micro channel 
ibm reaffirmed that it would come out with a personal computer 
built on intel corps latest microprocessor the highspeed i486 
by the end of the year it cut prices and introduced new variations 
on several existing models in its personal system2 line 
