<TEXT>
the citizens and southern corp and sovran 
financial corp announced a 47 billion merger tuesday that will 
create the nations 14thlargest bank 
camps based in atlanta and sovran based in norfolk va will 
have total assets of 47 billion and almost 1000 offices in seven 
states from maryland to florida and the district of columbia 
under a newly formed holding company called avantor financial 
corp the two banks will maintain dual headquarters and retain 
current management 
the merger comes five months after camps fought off a takeover bid 
by north carolinas ncnb corp unlike that proposal the campssovran 
deal is a friendly merger 
in a joint statement sovran chairman albert b gornto jr and 
camps chairman bennett a brown said the deal combines the advantages 
of size and market strength with success in communitybased banking 
we are creating a large nationally competitive franchise with 
a powerful presence in major highgrowth markets and were 
underwriting it with superior credit quality they said in a 
statement 
this is a company that will be completely focused on service 
efficiency and profitability the statement said 
the boards of the two companies have approved the agreement 
final approval from shareholders and federal and state regulators 
is expected in the first quarter of 1990 
both companies will remain in existence as subsidiaries of the 
new umbrella organization a new board of directors will be 
established with 15 members from sovran and 14 from camps 
its a big deal said lacy shockley a banking industry 
analyst with smith barney harris upham co in new york its 
going to create the powerhouse in the southeast 
camps has 489 bank offices in georgia florida and south carolina 
sovran has 487 offices in virginia maryland washington dc 
tennessee and kentucky 
scott scredon a camps spokesman in atlanta said the merger has 
been discussed on and off for about two years 
we feel its a perfect fit scredon said we dont overlap 
and we each double our market presence we both feel it 
couldnt be any better 
scredon said customers should not see any immediate changes when 
the merger is completed but once the two institutions pool 
resources new services probably will be offered 
under the merger agreement each of sovrans 598 million shares 
of outstanding common stock will convert into 123 shares of the 
new companys common stock each of campss 62 million shares of 
outstanding common stock will convert into 10 shares of the new 
companys common stock 
brown will become chairman and chief executive officer of the 
new company while retaining his position at camps gornto will become 
chairman of the new companys executive committee and will retain 
his position at the virginia bank 
dennis c bottorff sovrans president and chief operating 
officer will be president and chief operating officer of avantor 
and would become chief executive of the new company upon browns 
