<TEXT>
adolph coors great grandsons broke with a 
family tradition of never borrowing money to brew beer when they 
decided to buy most of stroh brewery co for 425 million 
but tradition is as strong as ever at coors where the coors men 
sit down to lunch every day in the dining room of the mansion 
adolph coors built more than a century ago on the brewery grounds 
as a 26yearold immigrant who left europe to avoid military 
service adolph coors founded a modest brewery on the banks of 
clear creek in 1873 just 14 years after goldseekers descended on 
the area 
but coors lacked the goldseekers gambling instincts his 
cardinal rules were to brew good beer and stay out of debt doing it 
over the years the founder passed on his cautious selfreliant 
streak to his son adolph coors jr and then to the grandsons 
william and joe coors the family business grew into the nations 
fourthlargest brewery 
the announcement monday that coors was going to pay 425 million 
for detroitbased strohs brewing assets represented a break with 
the past 
the deal will give coors 18 stroh brands five stroh breweries 
and two can plants if completed as expected early next year the 
acquisition will boost coors annual sales to nearly 3 billion 
coors would become the nations no 3 brewer behind anheuserbusch 
and miller 
to complete the deal coors will have to borrow an estimated 
300 million and because the coors family has assiduously avoided 
such borrowing throughout its history adolph coors co 
traditionally has paid cash when it wanted something the company 
has no bond rating 
still it is not expected to have trouble finding or repaying 
the money 
the company believes in a strong balance sheet if you have a 
strong balance sheet it enables you to make a move like we have 
with stroh rob klugman vice president of development for coors 
brewing co said tuesday 
the coors family controls 100 percent of adolph coors class a 
voting stock and about a third of its nonvoting publicly traded 
class b stock 
the stroh acquisition is a clear indication that the 
fourthgeneration coors brothers peter jeff and joe jr are 
firmly in control one year after the torch was passed by their 
uncle william coors and their father joe coors in a 
reorganization 
all five of joe coors sons attend to family business while 
peter coors 43 runs the beerbrewing operation and was the key 
figure in the stroh deal jeff coors 44 is president of adolph 
coors co and joe coors jr 46 the oldest son is head of coors 
porcelain cos 
the two other brothers grover 39 and john 33 have lesser 
roles in the family business grover heads microlithics a coors 
subsidiary that produces military systems and john is in charge of 
coors customer satisfaction division 
jeff joe and i are running the business said peter coors 
president of coors brewing co when asked what role his uncle 
william coors 73 the company chairman and joe coors 72 vice 
chairman continue to play in the firms daytoday operations 
despite the decision to incur major debt the coors family 
remains a strong believer in tradition every day that business 
does not take them out of town the brothers lunch inside the 
22room coors mansion the official family residence on the brewery 
grounds that adolph coors built 
that kind of traditionalism over the years has been reflected in 
the coors politically conservative image especially concerning 
organized labor 
a year after brewery workers union went on strike in 1977 over 
coors desire to subject its workers to liedetector tests coors 
replaced the strikers with nonunion employees that earned the 
company the enmity of national labor and triggered a national 
consumer boycott by the aflcio that lasted 10 years 
the boycott ended after coors pledged not to interfere with 
union organizing efforts at coors although brewery workers 
rejected the teamsters union in an election in december 1988 
joe coors a prominent conservative and friend of former 
president ronald reagan was an outspoken member of reagans 
socalled kitchen cabinet during reagans early presidential 
years 
an active supporter of anticommunist causes coors also 
testified on behalf of marine lt col oliver north at the senate 
irancontra hearings documents released during those hearings 
showed that a 65000 donation by coors wound up in a swiss bank 
account used to buy arms for nicaraguan rebels 
</TEXT>
