<TEXT>
a 425 million agreement in principle for 
adolph coors co to buy the no 3ranked stroh brewing cos brands 
and breweries sets up a big three among us beer makers 
analysts said 
coors president peter coors on monday announced his companys 
plans to acquire most of strohs assets and send a message to no 1 
anheuserbusch cos inc and no 2 miller brewing that coors is the 
one to be watched 
clearly we are in the beer business said coors head of the 
no 4 brewer in the nation if we are going to be in the beer 
business longterm weve got to be a major and significant 
competitor 
allan kaplan an analyst with merrill lynch amp co inc in new 
york said the sale will result in a big three of us brewing 
combining detroitbased stroh and goldenbased coors would 
produce a company with 187 percent of the market a tougher 
competitor for the top two and far ahead of the next g heileman 
brewing co which has about a 7 percent share 
jay nelson of brown brothers harriman amp co also of new york 
said that while the acquisition is not a sure thing it still 
faces several hurdles the combination would mean coors would 
compete better and benefit from economies of scale distribution 
and purchasing 
you may have more clout all along the line more bang for the 
buck in advertising and more bang for the buck in general he 
said 
i think the price is a good one for coors standpoint it 
looks cheap on the basis of replacement value of the breweries and 
theyre getting ongoing brands those brands are not generating a 
lot of income but consumers are buying them and theres some 
potential there nelson said 
coors officials said they expect to take nearly 20 percent of 
the beer market with the stroh acquisition and become stronger not 
only from a business standpoint but from a consumer standpoint 
the agreement would give coors most of stroh brewing cos 
brewing and container facilities and brands 
stroh brewing co will continue to exist but the operating 
company will not coors said golden will be headquarters for the 
entire operation 
the purchase by coors would be paid in part by the assumption of 
longterm debt and other selected liabilities with the balance 
paid in cash coors would not disclose the amount of either 
the plan would give coors the following brands strohs and 
strohs light signature schlitz schlitz light and schlitz malt 
liquor schaefer light and schaefer nonalcohol and lowalcohol 
brands old milwaukee and old milwaukee light red bull silver 
thunder and st barts a nonalcohol brand as well as the 
licensing rights to piels piels light and augsburger 
coors said he did not know which brands would be retained and 
which discarded 
primo a stroh beer brewed in hawaii and distributed in some 
west coast cities is not included and neither is sundance a wine 
cooler stroh also bottles other wine coolers and drinks that are 
not included the chairman said 
the move is part of a drive begun in the early 1980s by coors to 
expand from a regional to a national brewer the company now sells 
its products in 49 states and washington dc 
coors has 10 beer brands its main labels are coors and coors 
light 
stroh has been suffering its worst financial troubles since it 
went national by acquiring jos schlitz brewing co in 1982 
stroh was unable to make inroads on the growth of anheuser 
busch which dominates the industry with a 41 percent share of the 
national beer market far ahead of millers 21 percent and strohs 
11 percent miller is a unit of philip morris cos inc 
the 139yearold stroh has been looking for potential partners 
since february and announced aug 31 it was laying off 300 of its 
1500 whitecollar employees nationwide chairman peter stroh said 
the cuts were being made because the familyowned company had been 
unable to find a partner 
stroh also cut back support of civic and industry affairs and 
advertising including auto racing sponsorships 
coors would acquire stroh plants in st paul minn tampa 
fla winstonsalem nc longview texas and allentown pa 
can plants to be acquired are in winstonsalem and longview 
stroh also has breweries in memphis tenn and van nuys 
calif that will not be acquired coors said 
stroh plants are represented by the teamsters while coors 
workers rejected representation by the teamsters last december 
weve been in touch with the teamsters and will want to develop a 
relationship with them coors said 
the transaction is subject to the negotiation of a definitive 
agreement approval by the boards of directors of both companies 
and review by the justice department coors said closing is not 
expected before early next year 
</TEXT>
